    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. one more thing, i noticed there are a few tiny gaps and some small cracks forming between the sheets where they meet. should i just fill those with the same mud or is there something else i should use to make sure they stay closed up?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For those tiny gaps and small cracks between the sheets, using the same joint compound is usually sufficient, but you might want to use a setting-type compound for the initial filler. This compound sets up quickly, which is perfect for filling tight gaps and preventing them from reopening before the mud hardens. After filling, you can smooth over it with your standard all-purpose mud during the taping process.",
      "source": "target",
